03/06/2004
MITROVICA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Authorities in Kosovo on Wednesday (2 June) formally launched the restoration of an entire Serb village, destroyed during riots the mid-March. The project is part of an $11m reconstruction package. Baxhet Brejshori, minister of sport and the chairman of a government's commission for restoring Serb property, said work in Svinjare should be completed by mid-October. Residents have been moved to Mitrovica. (AFP - 02/06/04)
